20week%2C%20saying%20the%20redistricting%20process%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bbrutal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20about%20six%20weeks%2C%20the%20state%20legislature%20here%20in%20North%20Carolina%20is%20going%20to%20redraw%20the%20congressional%20map%2C%20and%20it%20looks%20like%20they%20will%20try%20to%20use%20that%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20take%20me%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Jackson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20majority%20party%20in%20the%20state%20legislature%20wants%20one%20of%20their%20own%20in%20this%20district%2C%20so%20they're%20going%20to%20bend%20it%20and%20stretch%20it%20to%20try%20and%20make%20that%20happen.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-gerrymandering-supreme-court-case-could-overhaul-american-elections-2017-10%5C%22%3EGerrymandering%3C%2Fa%3E%20refers%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20drawing%20political%20districts%20that%20give%20one%20party%20a%20lopsided%20advantage%20over%20the%20other%20in%20an%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoundaries%20for%20state%20and%20federal%20districts%20are%20redrawn%20every%2010%20years%20following%20the%20federal%20census%20to%20ensure%20each%20district%20contains%20roughly%20the%20same%20number%20of%20people.%20Usually%2C%20the%20party%20in%20power%20is%20the%20one%20in%20control%20of%20the%20redistricting%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20both%20Republicans%20and%20Democrats%20have%20benefited%20from%20gerrymandering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20round%20of%20redistricting%2C%2026%20states%20approved%20maps%20on%20a%20partisan%20basis%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brennancenter.org%2Four-work%2Fresearch-reports%2Fwho-controlled-redistricting-every-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrennan%20Center%20for%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%202022.%20Just%20four%20states%20%E2%80%94%20Arizona%2C%20California%2C%20Colorado%2C%20and%20Michigan%20%E2%80%94%20used%20fully%20independent%20commissions%20to%20draw%20their%20maps.%20In%20an%20opinion%20in%20June%2C%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-upholds-ban-racial-gerrymandering-alabama-2023-6%5C%22%3EAlabama%20violated%20the%20Voting%20Rights%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20creating%20congressional%20districts%20that%20discriminated%20against%20Black%20voters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20when%20he%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20state's%20senate%2C%20Jackson%20filed%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwebservices.ncleg.gov%2FViewBillDocument%2F2015%2F128%2F0%2FDRS35008-TH-3C%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebill%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20establish%20an%20independent%20redistricting%20commission%20in%20North%20Carolina%20to%20draw%20voting%20districts%20instead%20of%20the%20state's%20lawmakers.%20But%20that%20bill%20never%20made%20it%20out%20of%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20video%2C%20Jackson%20said%20it%20wasn't%20a%20shock%20to%20him%20that%20he'd%20be%20targeted%20by%20redistricting%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20doesn't%20think%20he%20will%20be%20the%20only%20Democrat%20impacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20can%20happen%20in%20states%20where%20politicians%20are%20allowed%20to%20draw%20the%20political%20map%2C%20which%20is%20a%20bad%20system%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20states%20don't%20allow%20it%2C%20and%20when%20I%20was%20in%20the%20state%20legislature%2C%20the%20first%20bill%20I%20ever%20filed%20was%20to%20ban%20politicians%20from%20being%20able%20to%20draw%20the%20map%2C%20and%20they%20sent%20that%20bill%20to%20a%20committee%20that%20hasn't%20met%20in%20over%2020%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Jackson%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Jackson's%20office%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%C2%A0Reached%20for%20comment%20via%20email%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20North%20Carolina%20General%20Assembly's%20Republican%20caucus%2C%2