report%20in%20late%20August%20that%20someone%20had%20created%20a%20gap%20in%20one%20of%20China's%20most%20famous%20historical%20structures%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F04%2Fchina%2Fchina-great-wall-damage-excavator-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%20reported%20Monday%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20CCTV%2C%20the%20Chinese%20state%20broadcaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pair%20reportedly%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20path%20cutting%20through%20the%20Ming-dynasty%20portion%20of%20the%20wall%20as%20a%20shortcut%2C%20according%20to%20CNN.%20The%20damage%20has%20affected%20the%20structural%20integrity%20of%20that%20portion%20of%20the%20Great%20Wall%2C%20and%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bbeyond%20repair%2C%26quot%3B%20state-owned%20newspaper%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chinadaily.com.cn%2Fa%2F202309%2F04%2FWS64f5a6aca310d2dce4bb3d00.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20Daily%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20happened%20in%20the%20Shanxi%20province%20in%20Northeastern%20China%2C%20according%20to%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20earliest%20segments%20of%20the%20Great%20Wall%2C%20which%20stretches%20for%20over%204%2C000%20miles%20across%20China%2C%20were%20first%20created%20in%20the%20third%20century%20BC.%20Later%20portions%20were%20added%20over%20the%20following%20centuries.%20The%20wall%20became%20a%20UNESCO%20World%20Heritage%20site%20in%201987.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wall%20has%20faced%20numerous%20sources%20of%20destruction%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20from%20careless%20tourists%20to%20desertification%20and%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Ftravel%2Fthe-great-wall-of-china-is-under-siege-825452%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2008%20article%20in%20Smithsonian%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20cited%20experts%20who%20claimed%20that%20up%20to%20two-