%20%24423%20billion%20annually%2C%20according%20to%20a%20UN%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFrom%20New%20York%20to%20Antarctica%2C%20non-native%20plants%20and%20wildlife%20are%20popping%20up%20more%20frequently%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we're%20contributing%20to%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHere%20are%205%20of%20the%20most%20obvious%20examples%20of%20how%20invasive%20species%20are%20impacting%20all%20of%20us%20right%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Antarctica%20to%20New%20York%20City%2C%20invasive%20species%20are%20becoming%20an%20increasingly%20rampant%20problem%20around%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20are%20directly%20contributing%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipbes.net%2FIASmediarelease%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20report%20from%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E%20details%20how%20humans%20have%20unleashed%20more%20than%2037%2C000%20invasive%20species%20into%20new%20territories%2C%20where%20they%20are%20crushing%20the%20competition%20and%20threatening%20the%20future%20of%20humanity%20as%20we%20know%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20this%20is%20going%20to%20sound%20grandiose%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Stoett%20%E2%80%94%20an%20Ontario%20Tech%20University%20professor%20who%20co-authored%20the%20new%20UN%20report%20along%20with%2085%20other%20experts%20from%2049%20different%20countries%20around%20the%20globe%20%E2%80%94%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fclimate-environment%2F2023%2F09%2F04%2Finvasive-species-un-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0before%20calling%20the%20specter%20of%20invasive%20species%20a%20%26quot%3Btremendous%20threat%26quot%3B%20to%20all%20of%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20civilization.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%201970%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20invasive%20species%20invasions%20has%20quadrupled%20every%20decade%2C%20and%20this%20new%20report%20estimates%20that%20they're%20now%20costing%20the%20world%20more%20than%20%24423%20billion%20each%20year%2C%20an%20estimate%20which%20Stoett%20qualified%20as%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20conservative.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20money%20we're%20losing.%20Scientists%20say%20invasive%20species%20are%20one%20of%20the%20top%20five%20drivers%20of%20biodiversity%20loss%20worldwide%20(alongside%20other%20environmental%20issues%20like%20pollution%20and%20climate%20change).%20The%20Intergovernmental%20Platform%20on%20Biodiversity%20and%20Ecosystem%20Services%20(IPBES)%2C%20the%20body%20which%20created%20the%20report%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20severe%20global%20threat%20posed%20by%20invasive%20alien%20species%20is%20underappreciated%2C%20underestimated%2C%20and%20often%20unacknowledged%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20impacts%20everything%20from%20our%20drinking%20water%2C%20to%20food%20availability%2C%20and%20mosquito%20breeding%20opportunities.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20still%20in%20any%20doubt%2C%20here%20are%20five%20obvious%20ways%20you%20can%20physically%20see%20the%20threat%20of%20invasive%20species%20playing%20out%20in%20real-time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESpotted%20lanternflies%20from%20China%20are%20jumping%20all%20over%20the%20East%20Coast%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20spotted%20lanternflies%20stand%20on%20a%20railing%20next%20to%20the%20Hudson%20River%20as%20the%20sun%20sets%20on%20the%20skyline%20of%20lower%20Manhattan%20in%20New%20York%20City%20on%20August%2026%2C%202023%2C%20in%20Jersey%20City%2C%20New%20Jersey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f64cf3781926001910fe21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221381%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpotted%20lanternflies%20eyeing%20the%20New%20York%20City%20skyline%20from%20in%20New%20Jersey%20(August%202023).%3Cp%3EGary%20Hershorn%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpotted%20lanternflies%2C%20native%20to%20China%2C%20were%20first%20spotted%20in%20the%20US%20in%202014%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aphis.usda.gov%2Faphis%2Fourfocus%2Fplanthealth%2Fplant-pest-and-disease-programs%2Fpests-and-diseases%2Fsa_insects%2Fslf%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDetection%2520History%2Cto%2520restrict%2520the%2520pest%2527s%2520movement.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20recorded%20them%20traveling%20to%20at%20least%2013%20more%20states%2C%20including%20New%20York%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20Michigan%2C%20and%20Ohio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELanternflies%20and%20their%20eggs%20are%20great%20hitchhikers%2C%20and%20humans%20are%20helping%20them%20thrive%20in%20the%20eastern%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Spotted%20lanternfly%20eggs%20are%20shown%20attached%20to%20a%20tree%20at%20Inwood%20Hill%20Park%20on%20September%2026%2C%202022%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20Spotted%20lanternflies%2C%20an%20insect%20native%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%20that%20scientists%20say%20arrived%20in%20the%20U.S.%20seven%20years%20ago%20and%20in%20New%20York%20City%20in%202020%2C%20feed%20on%20the%20sap%20of%20more%20than%2070%20plant%20species%2C%20leaving%20them%20susceptible%20to%20disease%20and%20destruction.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f64cf1781926001910fe0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpotted%20lanternfly%20eggs%20attached%20to%20a%20tree%20at%20Inwood%20Hill%20Park%20in%20New%20York%20City%20(September%2026%2C%202022).%3Cp%3EMichael%20M.%20Santiago%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20at%20Cornell%20University%20suspect%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcals.cornell.edu%2Fnew-york-state-integrated-pest-management%2Foutreach-education%2Fwhats-bugging-you%2Fspotted-lanternfly%2Fspotted-lanternfly-biology-and-lifecycle%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMating%2520takes%2520place%2520starting%2520in%2Cuntil%2520the%2520first%2520killing%2520freeze.%26amp%3Btext%3DSpotted%2520lanternflies%2520begin%2520to%2520hatch%2Cand%2520black%2520with%2520white%2520spots.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20main%20reason%20lanternflies%20haven't%20been%20stamped%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20yet%20in%20the%20US%20is%20because%20they%20are%20constantly%20being%20accidentally%20transported%20by%20people%2C%20whether%20by%20flying%20into%20their%20cars%20or%20hitching%20a%20ride%20on%20wood%20that%20then%20gets%20moved%20around.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20human%20help%2C%20lanternflies%20have%20a%20jumping%20and%20flying%20range%20of%20only%20about%20three%20to%20four%20miles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20recent%20fires%20in%20Maui%20were%20also%20fueled%20by%20a%20non-native%20invasive%20grass%20species%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marine%20One%2C%20carrying%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20flies%20above%20wildfire%20damage%20in%20Lahaina%20on%20the%20island%20of%20Maui%2C%20in%20Hawaii%20on%20August%2021%2C%202023.%20The%20Bidens%20are%20expected%20to%20meet%20with%20first%20responders%2C%20survivors%2C%20and%20local%20officials%20following%20deadly%20wildfires%20in%20Maui.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f64cf2781926001910fe13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20surveyed%20fire%20damage%20from%20above%20Maui%20in%20Marine%20One%20on%20August%2021%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EMandel%20Ngan%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGuinea%20grass%20is%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20everywhere%20you%20go%2C%20unfortunately%2C%26quot%3B%20O'ahu's%20Waimea%20Valley%20Volunteer%20Coordinator%20Melani%20Spielman%20said%20in%20a%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DVSN_CXwEJek%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20YouTube%3C%2Fa%3E%20video%20posted%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20that%20super%20tall%20grass%20you%20see%20all%20along%20the%20roadsides%2C%20up%20in%20the%20mountains%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20saw%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmaui-wildfires-service-cell-service-landlines-down-hawaii-2023-8%5C%22%3Edeadly%20wildfires%20that%20ravaged%20Maui%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%2C%20killing%20people%20and%20wildlife%2C%20this%20tall%20grass%20can%20propel%20fires.%20In%20turn%2C%20it%20helps%20kill%20off%20more%20native%20species%20that%20are%20not%20so%20fire-adapted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20fire%20dangers%2C%20it's%20also%20got%20little%20bitty%20hairs%20at%20the%20base%20of%20the%20plant%20that%20can%20aggravate%20your%20skin%20if%20you%20rub%20up%20against%20it.%20Some%20people%20call%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ctahr.hawaii.edu%2Finvweed%2FWeedsHI%2FW_Panicum_maximum.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bgreen%20panic%20grass.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETall%20Guinea%20Grass%20is%20local%20to%20parts%20of%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20and%20it%20was%20introduced%20to%20Hawaii%20in%20the%201700s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%226%20year%20old%20Tya%2C%20a%20chimpanzee%2C%20looks%20out%20of%20the%20grass%20during%20a%20bushwalk%20at%20the%20Chimpanzee%20Conservation%20Centre%20(CCC)%20on%20November%2030%2C%202015%20in%20Somoria%2C%20Guinea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f64eb1781926001910feb0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20grass%20is%20native%20to%20parts%20of%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20including%20this%20chimpanzee's%20home%20in%20Somoria%2C%20Guinea.%3Cp%3EDan%20Kitwood%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fsmart-news%2Fhow-swaths-of-invasive-grass-made-mauis-fires-so-devastating-180982729%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERanchers%20living%20in%20Hawaii%3C%2Fa%3E%20brought%20the%20grass%20there%20because%20it%20was%20a%20drought-resistant%20way%20to%20make%20sure%20their%20animals%20stayed%20fed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20stress%20that%20most%20non-native%20and%20introduced%20plants%20are%20not%20invasive.%20The%20authors%20of%20the%20new%20UN%20report%20estimate%20that%20only%20about%206%25%20of%20non-native%20plants%20and%2011%25%20of%20non-native%20microbes%20are%20invasive%20species.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20invasive%20species%20are%20an%20outsized%20driver%20of%20animal%20and%20plant%20extinctions%2C%20contributing%20to%20over%20half%20(60%25)%20of%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20most%20widespread%20invasive%20species%20worldwide%20is%20a%20pretty%2C%20purple-flowered%20water%20plant%20from%20South%20America%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Flowering%20water%20hyacinths%20in%20a%20wetland%20near%20the%20Piuval%20Lodge%20in%20the%20Northern%20Pantanal%2C%20State%20of%20Mato%20Grosso%2C%20Brazil.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f676187819260019110543%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221399%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFlowering%20water%20hyacinths%20are%20native%20to%20Brazil.%3Cp%3EWolfgang%20Kaehler%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20lakes%20in%20Kenya%20to%20the%20waters%20of%20Bangladesh%20and%20the%20US%20state%20of%20Florida%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmyfwc.com%2Fwildlifehabitats%2Fhabitat%2Finvasive-plants%2Fweed-alerts%2Fwater-hyacinth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20water%20hyacinth%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20native%20to%20South%20America%20%E2%80%94%20has%20caused%20serious%20problems%20for%20fishermen%20locally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20block%20entire%20waterways%2C%20crowding%20out%20other%20plants%2C%20and%20it%20makes%20a%20great%20breeding%20ground%20for%20mosquitoes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EZebra%20mussels%20from%20Europe%20have%20threatened%20drinking%20water%20and%20power%20plants%20in%20the%20US%20Great%20Lakes%20region%20since%20they%20were%20introduced%20in%20the%201980s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22September%2023%2C%202011%20photo%20shows%20a%20man%20holding%20a%20handful%20of%20Zebra%20mussels%20near%20Kingston%2C%20Canada%2C%20which%20have%20invaded%20Lake%20Ontario.%20Zebra%20mussels%20from%20the%20Caspian%20Sea%2C%20introduced%20to%20North%20America%20by%20accident%2C%20are%20becoming%20a%20veritable%20plague%20releasing%20toxic%20chemicals%20into%20the%20Great%20Lakes%2C%20Canadian%20biologists%20say.%20The%20mussels%20hitch-hiked%20to%20Canada%20on%20the%20ballasts%20of%20cargo%20ships%20arriving%20on%20the%20continent%20in%201986.%20And%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20the%20thumbnail-sized%20creatures%20have%20spread%20and%20are%20found%20in%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%20the%20Great%20Lakes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f64cf3781926001910fe1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZebra%20mussels%20near%20Lake%20Ontario%20in%20Canada.%3Cp%3EKilian%20Fichou%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EZebra%20mussels%20are%20great%20at%20latching%20on%20to%20almost%20anything%2C%20from%20a%20boat%20propeller%20to%20a%20rock%2C%20and%20they%20outcompete%20local%20mussels%20in%20the%20Great%20Lakes%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20think%20that%20zebra%20mussels%20were%20probably%20introduced%20to%20North%20America%20when%20big%20boats%20traveling%20from%20Europe%20discharged%20water%20from%20across%20the%20Atlantic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20mussels%20regularly%20clog%20pipes%20at%20power%20plants%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usgs.gov%2Ffaqs%2Fwhat-are-zebra-mussels-and-why-should-we-care-about-them%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresulting%20in%20millions%20of%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20damage.%20They%20once%20forced%20a%20water%20pump%20supplying%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.des.nh.gov%2Fsites%2Fg%2Ffiles%2Fehbemt341%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2020-01%2Fbb-17.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrinking%20water%20to%2050%2C000%20Michigan%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20shut%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEven%20Antarctica%20isn't%20safe%20from%20the%20threat%20of%20invaders%20like%20a%20non-native%20bluegrass%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22stalks%20of%20green%20and%20white%20meadow%20grass%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f673281b7ced0019c7e14d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPoa%20annua%20is%20an%20annual%20bluegrass%20species%20native%20to%20Eurasia.%3Cp%3EHu%20Weibin%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20worried%20that%20as%20the%20poles%20warm%2C%20invasive%20grasses%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fneobiota.pensoft.net%2Farticle%2F37250%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20common%20Eurasian%20bluegrass%20called%20%26quot%3Bpoa%20annua%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7182586%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrowd%20out%20the%20local%20grasses%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Antarctica%20entirely%2C%20killing%20them%20off%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20experts%20assure%20that%20we%20can%20take%20preventative%20measures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%2C%20for%20almost%20every%20context%20and%20situation%2C%20there%20are%20management%20tools%2C%20governance%20options%2C%20and%20targeted%20actions%20that%20really%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anibal%20Pauchard%2C%20a%20professor%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Concepci%C3%B3n%2C%20in%20Chile%2C%20who%20co-chaired%20the%20new%20UN%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrevention%20is%20absolutely%20the%20best%2C%20most%20cost-effective%20option%20%E2%80%94%20but%20eradication%2C%20containment%2C%20and%20control%20are%20also%20effective%20in%20specific%20contexts.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-invasive-species-threaten-the-future-of-humanity-un-report-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693874099000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f669bb7819260019110102%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-invasive-species-threaten-the-future-of-humanity-un-report-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20United%20Nations%20report%20says%20invasive%20species%20are%20costing%20the%20world%20%24423%20billion%20every%20year%20to%20combat.%20And%20we%20are%20part%20of%20the%20problem.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbrueck%40businessinsider.com%20(Hilary%20Brueck)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-invasive-species-threaten-the-future-of-humanity-un-report-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taiwan%20president%20leaves%20for%20visit%20to%20last%20African%20ally%20Eswatini%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693873563000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-1