%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fcoup-de-chance-review-woody-allen-venice-film-festival-1235712530%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fcoup-de-chance-review-woody-allen-venice-film-festival-1235712530%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fcoup-de-chance-review-woody-allen-venice-film-festival-1235712530%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2237%2C000%20Alien%20Species%20Catalogued%2C%20Cost%20Humans%20%24423%20Billion%20Per%20Year%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EInvasive%20species%20that%20wreck%20crops%2C%20ravage%20forests%2C%20spread%20disease%2C%20and%20upend%20ecosystems%20are%20spreading%20ever%20faster%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20and%20humanity%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20stem%20the%20tide%2C%20a%20major%20scientific%20assessment%20said%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20failure%20is%20costing%20well%20over%20%24400%20billion%20dollars%20a%20year%20in%20damages%20and%20lost%20income%20--%20the%20equivalent%20to%20the%20GDP%20of%20Denmark%20or%20Thailand%20--%20and%20that%20is%20likely%20a%20%26quot%3Bgross%20underestimation%26quot%3B%2C%20according%20to%20the%20intergovernmental%20science%20advisory%20panel%20for%20the%20UN%20Convention%20on%20Biodiversity%20(IPBES).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20water%20hyacinth%20choking%20Lake%20Victoria%20in%20East%20Africa%2C%20to%20rats%20and%20brown%20snakes%20wiping%20out%20bird%20species%20in%20the%20Pacific%2C%20to%20mosquitoes%20exposing%20new%20regions%20to%20Zika%2C%20yellow%20fever%2C%20dengue%20and%20other%20diseases%2C%20the%20report%20catalogued%20more%20than%2037%2C000%20so-called%20alien%20species%20that%20have%20taken%20root%20--%20often%20literally%20--%20far%20from%20their%20places%20of%20origin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20number%20is%20trending%20sharply%20upward%2C%20along%20with%20the%20bill%20for%20the%20damage%20multiplying%20fourfold%20per%20decade%2C%20on%20average%2C%20since%201970.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomic%20expansion%2C%20population%20increase%20and%20climate%20change%20%26quot%3Bwill%20increase%20the%20frequency%20and%20extent%20of%20biological%20invasions%20and%20the%20impacts%20of%20invasive%20alien%20species%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%2017%20percent%20of%20countries%20have%20laws%20or%20regulations%20to%20manage%20this%20onslaught%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20by%20accident%20or%20on%20purpose%2C%20when%20non-native%20species%20wind%20up%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20world%2C%20humans%20are%20to%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spread%20of%20species%20is%20hard%20evidence%20that%20the%20rapid%20expansion%20of%20human%20activity%20has%20so%20radically%20altered%20natural%20systems%20as%20to%20tip%20the%20Earth%20into%20a%20new%20geological%20epoch%2C%20the%20Anthropocene%2C%20scientists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHitchhikers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hyacinth%20that%20at%20one%20point%20covered%2090%20percent%20of%20Lake%20Victoria%20--%20crippling%20transport%2C%20smothering%20aquatic%20life%2C%20blocking%20hydroelectric%20dam%20intake%20and%20breeding%20mosquitoes%20--%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20been%20introduced%20by%20Belgian%20colonial%20officials%20in%20Rwanda%20as%20an%20ornamental%20garden%20flower%20before%20making%20its%20way%20down%20the%20Kagera%20River%20in%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Florida%20Everglades%20is%20teeming%20with%20the%20destructive%20offspring%20of%20erstwhile%20pets%20and%20house%20plants%2C%20from%20five-metre%20(16-foot)%20Burmese%20pythons%20and%20walking%20catfish%20to%20Old%20World%20climbing%20fern%20and%20Brazilian%20pepper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2019th%20century%20English%20settlers%20brought%20rabbits%20to%20New%20Zealand%20to%20hunt%20and%20for%20food.%20When%20they%20multiplied%20like%2C%20well%2C%20rabbits%2C%20officials%20imported%20ferocious%20little%20carnivores%20called%20stoats%20to%20reduce%20their%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20stoats%20went%20after%20easier%20prey%3A%20dozens%20of%20endemic%20bird%20species%20that%20were%20soon%20decimated%2C%20from%20baby%20Kiwis%20to%20wrybills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Zealand%20and%20Australia%20--%20where%20a%20similar%20bad-to-worse%20saga%20involving%20rabbits%20unfolded%20--%20are%20%26quot%3Bcase%20studies%26quot%3B%20of%20how%20not%20to%20control%20one%20imported%20pest%20with%20another%2C%20Elaine%20Murphy%2C%20a%20scientist%20at%20New%20Zealand's%20Department%20of%20Conservation%2C%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20often%2C%20however%2C%20invasive%20species%20are%20accidental%20arrivals%2C%20hitching%20rides%20in%20the%20ballast%20water%20of%20cargo%20ships%2C%20the%20containers%20in%20their%20holds%2C%20or%20in%20a%20tourist's%20suitcase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mediterranean%20Sea%20is%20full%20of%20non-native%20fish%20and%20plants%2C%20such%20as%20lionfish%20and%20killer%20alga%2C%20that%20journeyed%20from%20the%20Red%20Sea%20through%20the%20Suez%20Canal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVulnerable%20small%20islands%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMurder%20hornets%20capable%20of%20wiping%20out%20entire%20bee%20colonies%20in%20a%20single%20attack%20are%20thought%20to%20have%20arrived%20in%20the%20US%20from%20Asia%20as%20stowaways%20in%20freight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELargely%20due%20to%20huge%20volumes%20of%20trade%2C%20Europe%20and%20North%20America%20have%20the%20world's%20largest%20concentrations%20of%20invasive%20species%2C%20defined%20as%20those%20that%20are%20non-native%20and%20cause%20harm%20and%20have%20relocated%20due%20to%20human%20activity%2C%20the%20IPBES%20report%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvasive%20species%20are%20a%20significant%20cause%20in%2060%20percent%20of%20all%20documented%20plant%20or%20animal%20extinctions%2C%20one%20of%20five%20main%20drivers%20along%20with%20habitat%20loss%2C%20global%20warming%20and%20pollution%2C%20according%20to%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20drivers%20interact%3A%20climate%20change%20has%20pushed%20alien%20species%20into%20newly%20warmed%20waters%20or%20lands%20where%20native%20species%20are%20often%20vulnerable%20to%20intruders%20they%20have%20never%20encountered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deadly%20fire%20that%20reduced%20the%20Hawaiian%20town%20of%20Lahaina%20on%20Maui%20to%20ashes%20last%20month%20was%20fuelled%20in%20part%20by%20bone-dry%20grasses%20--%20imported%20decades%20ago%20to%20feed%20livestock%20--%20that%20has%20spread%20across%20abandoned%20sugar%20plantations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20global%20treaty%20to%20protect%20biodiversity%20hammered%20out%20in%20Montreal%20last%20December%20sets%20a%20target%20of%20reducing%20the%20rate%20at%20which%20invasive%20alien%20species%20spread%20by%20half%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IPBES%20report%20lays%20out%20general%20strategies%20for%20achieving%20this%20goal%2C%20but%20does%20not%20assess%20the%20chances%20of%20it%20being%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20basically%20three%20lines%20of%20defence%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%20--%20prevention%2C%20eradication%20and%20then%2C%20failing%20that%2C%20containment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttempts%20at%20eradication%20have%20generally%20failed%20in%20large%20bodies%20of%20water%20and%20open%20waterways%2C%20as%20well%20as%20on%20large%20tracts%20of%20contiguous%20land.%20The%20places%20with%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20success%20in%20removing%20unwanted%20guests%20--%20especially%20rats%20and%20other%20vertebrates%20--%20are%20also%20the%20ones%20that%20have%20proved%20most%20vulnerable%3A%20small%20islands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693855560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fg504jds8_invasive