sc-not-just-a-poly-vocal-court-but-a-people-centric-one-says-cji%2Farticle67224683.ece%5C%22%3Espeech%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20August%2022%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20said%20that%20one%20of%20the%20missions%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Collegium%20was%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20richness%20and%20diversity%20of%20India%20were%20represented%20in%20the%20highest%20court.%20He%20claimed%20that%20some%20people%20criticise%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20being%20a%20polyvocal%20court%2C%20but%20he%20would%20rather%20consider%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpeople-centric%20court%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20is%20not%20unusual%20for%20a%20judge%20from%20Maharashtra%20sitting%20on%20a%20bench%20with%20a%20judge%20from%20West%20Bengal%20to%20determine%20a%20case%20from%20Haryana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20CJI%20may%20indeed%20be%20correct%20in%20describing%20the%20court%20as%20a%20people-centric%20court%2C%20the%20perception%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20a%20polyvocal%20court%20has%20gained%20currency%20in%20recent%20years%20because%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20are%20too%20many%20judges%20sitting%20in%20different%20benches%20interpreting%20the%20law%20and%20the%20constitution%20in%20conflicting%20terms%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20uncertainty%20and%20incoherence%20as%20to%20the%20correct%20legal%20position%20on%20any%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20comprising%20Justices%20M.M.%20Sundresh%20and%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fsupreme-court-reservations-gautam-navlakha-house-arrest-order%5C%22%3Eorally%20observed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20order%20to%20allow%20a%20plea%20by%20activist%20Gautam%20Navlakha%2C%20for%20his%20house%20arrest%2C%20did%20not%20deal%20with%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20overall%20case%20and%20proceedings%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20two-judge%20bench%2C%20comprising%20Justices%20K.M.%20Joseph%20(who%20has%20since%20retired)%20and%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%2C%20had%20on%20November%2010%20last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-allows-transfer-of-bhima-koregaon-accused-gautam-navlakha-to-house-arrest-for-one-month-imposes-conditions-213754%5C%22%3Egranted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Navlakha%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20house%20arrest%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20medical%20reports%20and%20his%20age%20(70%20years).%20The%20bench%20had%20noted%20that%20the%20trial%20of%20the%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20case%2C%20in%20which%20he%20is%20an%20accused%2C%20is%20unlikely%20to%20take%20place%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%20even%20as%20the%20charges%20have%20not%20been%20framed.%20To%20avail%20the%20facility%20of%20house%20arrest%2C%20the%20K.M.Joseph-Hrishikesh%20Roy%20bench%20had%20placed%20several%20restrictions%20on%20Navlakha%E2%80%99s%20freedom%2C%20and%20required%20him%20to%20provide%20local%20surety%20for%20a%20sum%20of%20Rs.2%20lakhs%2C%20with%20a%20caveat%20that%20any%20violation%20of%20the%20conditions%20imposed%20may%20result%20in%20cancellation%20of%20the%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20oral%20observation%20on%20Friday%20(September%201)%20by%20the%20M.M.%20Sundresh-J.B.%20Pardiwala%20bench%2C%20therefore%2C%20has%20led%20to%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20previous%20decision%20granting%20house%20arrest%20to%20Navlakha%20on%20medical%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20breaks%20down%20the%20issues%20associated%20with%20the%20perception%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20a%20polyvocal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20become%20a%20polyvocal%20court%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20constitution%20of%201950%20envisaged%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20with%20a%20Chief%20Justice%20and%20seven%20puisne%20judges%20%E2%80%93%20leaving%20it%20to%20parliament%20to%20increase%20this%20number.%20In%20the%20early%20years%2C%20all%20the%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20sat%20together%20to%20hear%20the%20cases%20presented%20before%20them.%20As%20the%20work%20of%20the%20court%20increased%20and%20arrears%20of%20cases%20began%20to%20accumulate%2C%20parliament%20increased%20the%20number%20of%20judges%20from%20eight%20in%201950%20to%2011%20in%201956%2C%2014%20in%201960%2C%2018%20in%201978%2C%2026%20in%201986%2C%2031%20in%202009%20and%2034%20in%202019%20(current%20strength).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20judges%20came%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20diversity%20of%20opinions%20and%20beliefs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20due%20to%20the%20heavy%20workload%20of%20cases%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20could%20not%20sit%20in%20benches%20that%20make%20up%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20total%20judges%2C%20instead%20they%20sit%20in%20smaller%20benches%20in%20pairs%20of%20two%20or%20groups%20of%20three%20and%20come%20together%20in%20larger%20benches%20of%20five%20and%20more%20only%20when%20required%20to%20do%20so%20or%20to%20settle%20a%20difference%20of%20opinion%2C%20or%20controversy.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20does%20not%20speak%20in%20one%20voice%20but%20with%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog-iacl-aidc.org%2Fcrisis-at-the-supreme-court-of-india%2F2018%2F5%2F20%2Fpotential-for-chaos-in-indias-polyvocal-supreme-court%5C%22%3E12%20or%2013%20different%20voices%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20legal%20scholar%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20advocate%2C%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20puts%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsunset-jobs-for-judges-and-the-question-of-judicial-independence%5C%22%3ESunset%20Jobs%20for%20Judges%20and%20the%20Question%20of%20Judicial%20Independence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20the%20Indian%20Supreme%20Court%20hailed%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%E2%80%99s%20court%E2%80%9D%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20scholar%20Nick%20Robinson%20writes%20that%20wide%20access%20also%20has%20clear%20practical%20benefits.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia-seminar.com%2F2013%2F642%2F642_nick_robinson.htm%5C%22%3Ewrites%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CTake%20the%20practice%20of%20admission%20day%2C%20where%20all%20cases%20filed%20before%20the%20court%20are%20briefly%20heard.%20Judges%20find%20that%20they%20can%20often%20determine%20more%20efficiently%20whether%20a%20case%20should%20receive%20a%20regular%20hearing%20through%20a%20short%20verbal%20exchange%20with%20a%20lawyer%20than%20by%20reading%20an%20often-wandering%20brief%20that%20may%20not%20adequately%20represent%20the%20issues%20at%20stake.%20More%20importantly%2C%20accepting%20a%20large%20number%20of%20cases%20for%20regular%20hearing%20allows%20the%20Indian%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20actively%20police%20the%20high%20courts%20and%20the%20lower%20judiciary.%20It%20also%20strengthens%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20check%20on%20the%20executive%20and%20legislature%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20make%20its%20presence%20known%20on%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20matters%20that%20might%20escape%20the%20attention%20of%20a%20less%20active%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20interventions%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcprindia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2FSSRN-id2061061.pdf%5C%22%3Eentitled%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20be%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%E2%80%99s%20court%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Clast%20resort%20for%20the%20oppressed%20and%20bewildered%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20powerful%20court%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwatch-arun-shourie-supreme-court-should-behave-as-if-its-at-war-with-executive-in-defence-of-constitution%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%3A%20Arun%20Shourie%E2%80%94Supreme%20Court%20Should%20Behave%20as%20if%20It%E2%80%99s%20at%20War%20With%20Executive%20in%20Defence%20of%20Constitution%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20a%20polyvocal%20court%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20invited%20criticism%20from%20scholars.%20Why%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20their%20respective%20views%2C%20and%20during%20hearings%20such%20differences%20appear%20quite%20starkly.%20Such%20differences%20in%20opinions%20especially%20arise%20in%20cases%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia-seminar.com%2F2013%2F642%2F642_nick_robinson.htm%5C%22%3EPILs%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20some%20judges%20believe%20in%20a%20stricter%20intervention%20in%20cases%20of%20lapses%20in%20governance%20while%20others%20rarely%20pursue%20intervention.%20Such%20differences%20in%20opinions%20and%20actions%20result%20in%20a%20confused%20production%20of%20doctrine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2019%2F10%2F15%2Faddendum-the-concept-of-bias-in-a-polyvocal-court%2F%5C%22%3EGautam%20Bhatia%3C%2Fa%3E%20argues%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20however%2C%20we%20have%20a%20situation%20where%20%3Cem%3Ewithin%20the%20highest%20judicial%20body%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20multiplicity%20of%20judicial%20panels%20undermines%20institutional%20coherence%20and%20creates%20a%20situation%20where%20the%20apex%20Court%20is%20effectively%20%3Cem%3Edisagreeing%20with%20itself%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20the%202000s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcprindia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2FSSRN-id2061061.pdf%5C%22%3EJustice%20Arijit%20Pasayat%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20known%20for%20handing%20out%20death%20penalty%20judgments%20in%20cases%20of%20heinous%20crimes%20such%20as%20rape%20and%20murder%2C%20and%20his%20bench%20frequently%20upheld%20death%20sentences%2C%20but%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Justice%20S.B.%20Sinha%20argued%20on%20the%20death%20penalty%E2%80%99s%20arbitrariness%20and%20his%20bench%20interpreted%20the%20death%20penalty%20doctrine%20such%20that%20it%20almost%20never%20applied.%20Legal%20predictability%20and%20stability%20are%20integral%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lexology.com%2Flibrary%2Fdetail.aspx%3Fg%3D13426387-176e-40be-9d5e-dc32cb2adbe5%5C%22%3Erule%20of%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20polyvocal%20courts%2C%20it%20becomes%20difficult%20to%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F01130806%2F15894769915_f3c72b86ef_k.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F01130806%2F15894769915_f3c72b86ef_k.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F01130806%2F15894769915_f3c72b86ef_k-300x161.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F01130806%2F15894769915_f3c72b86ef_k-1024x548.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-401529%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22642%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20Flickr%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20important%20issue%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flddashboard.legislative.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FA2013-30.pdf%5C%22%3Enew%20land%20acquisition%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20introduced%20in%20India%20in%202013.%20The%20controversial%20part%20was%20Section%2024%20of%20the%202013%20Act%20which%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20in%20land%20acquisition%20proceedings%2C%20compensation%20had%20not%20been%20deposited%20in%20the%20accounts%20of%20the%20beneficiaries%20for%20a%20period%20of%20five%20years%20from%20the%20date%20of%20the%20award%2C%20the%20proceedings%20would%20lapse%2C%20and%20the%20land%20be%20returned%20to%20the%20owners.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20dispute%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog-iacl-aidc.org%2Fcrisis-at-the-supreme-court-of-india%2F2018%2F5%2F20%2Fpotential-for-chaos-in-indias-polyvocal-supreme-court%5C%22%3Ecentred%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20what%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cdeposit%E2%80%9D%20meant.%20Three%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20ruled%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2FPuneMunicipalCorp_2014.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202014%20that%20the%20clause%20required%20the%20compensation%20to%20at%20least%20be%20deposited%20in%20court%20rather%20than%20just%20the%20government%20treasury.%20In%20deciding%20matters%20involving%20land%20acquisition%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20issued%20at%20least%2017%20documented%20decisions%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20following%20three%20years%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20decisions%20from%20different%20state%20high%20courts.%20This%20case%20was%20decided%20by%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20comprising%20the%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20R.M.%20Lodha%20and%20Justices%20Madan%20B.%20Lokur%20and%20Kurian%20Joseph%2C%20and%20the%20judgment%20was%20authored%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20Lodha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20February%202018%2C%20a%20different%20three-judge%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20disagreed%20(in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2FIndoreJudgement_08-Feb-20181.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndore%20Development%20Authority%20v%20Shailendra%20(Dead%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E)%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20sufficient%20for%20the%20money%20to%20be%20paid%20into%20the%20treasury.%20This%20bench%20consisted%20of%20Justices%20Arun%20Mishra%2C%20Adarsh%20Kumar%20Goel%20and%20the%20late%20Mohan%20M.%20Shantanagoudar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Arun%20Mishra%20authored%20the%20judgment%2C%20while%20Justice%20Shantanagoudar%20wrote%20a%20dissent%20note%2C%20saying%20the%20case%20ought%20to%20be%20referred%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20for%20being%20assigned%20to%20a%20larger%20bench%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20previous%20decision%20of%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20in%20%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F185065833%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20case%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20court%20had%20held%20that%20land%20acquisition%20could%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farun-mishra-judicial-indiscipline-supreme-court%5C%22%3Edeclared%20void%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20section%2024(2)%20of%20the%20Land%20Acquisition%20Act%20of%202013%20%E2%80%9Cif%20compensation%20had%20not%20been%20deposited%20in%20the%20bank%20accounts%20of%20the%20landowners%20or%20with%20the%20court.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndore%20Development%20Authority%20(2018)%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%20the%20Mishra%20bench%20ruled%20against%20the%20same%2C%20without%20any%20regard%20to%20judicial%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20in%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20cases%2C%20the%20government%20was%20no%20longer%20required%20to%20return%20the%20land%20it%20had%20acquired%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation.%3C%2Fem%3E%20In%20order%20to%20resolve%20their%20disagreement%20because%20they%20were%20bound%20by%20the%20decision%20of%20a%20coordinate%20bench%2C%20the%20three%20judges%20would%20typically%20have%20had%20to%20document%20their%20disagreement%20and%20ask%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20to%20appoint%20a%20bigger%20bench%20(of%20five%20judges).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArguing%20that%20%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20%3Cem%3Eper%20curiam%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20hence%20not%20a%20legally%20binding%20judgment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fthe-nation%2Farticle29897723.ece%5C%22%3Etwo%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20three%20judges%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndore%20Development%20Authority%20(2018)%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%20Justices%20Arun%20Misra%20and%20Adarsh%20Kumar%20Goel%20determined%20they%20did%20not%20need%20to%20do%20that.%20It%E2%80%99s%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20the%20third%20judge%20refused%20to%20declare%20%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20%3Cem%3Eper%20curiam%3C%2Fem%3E%20even%20though%20he%20agreed%20with%20the%20other%20two%20judges%E2%80%99%20interpretation%20of%20section%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20obvious%20explanation%20for%20this%20is%20that%20the%20notion%20of%20%3Cem%3Eper%20curiam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20in%20common%20law%20nullifies%20a%20judgment%2C%20is%20only%20occasionally%20employed.%20Its%20use%20is%20only%20permitted%20when%20a%20judgment%20disregards%20a%20rule%20of%20law%20that%20was%20binding%20on%20it%20or%20a%20precedent%20that%20was%20also%20binding.%20In%20actuality%2C%20the%20two%20judges%20in%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indore%20Development%20Authority%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2018)%20case%20were%20unable%20to%20prove%20this%3B%20their%20chief%20argument%20was%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20disregarded%20a%20number%20of%20regulations%20outlined%20in%20the%20previous%20Land%20Acquisition%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Justice%20Shantanagoudar%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20the%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20not%20rendered%20%3Cem%3Eper%20incuriam%3C%2Fem%3E%20(as%20held%20by%20the%20other%20two%20judges%20on%20the%20bench)%20as%20the%20conclusion%20was%20reached%20by%20proceeding%20in%20detail%20on%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%20relevant%20statutory%20provisions.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20suggested%20that%20the%20proper%20course%20before%20the%20bench%20was%20to%20refer%20the%20matter%20to%20a%20larger%20bench%20as%20a%20bench%20must%20follow%20the%20decision%20of%20a%20coordinate%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20later%20referred%20to%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20led%20by%20Justice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fcases%2Findore-development-authority-manoharlal-land-acquisition-case-background%2F%5C%22%3EArun%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2FLand_Acquisition_Judgment.pdf%5C%22%3Eoverturned%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EPune%20Municipal%20Corporation%20%3C%2Fem%3Ejudgment.%20It%20was%20argued%20by%20many%20that%20there%20was%20an%20apparent%20bias%20in%20the%20judgment%20being%20reviewed%20by%20the%20same%20judge%20who%20handed%20it.%20In%20effect%2C%20judicial%20bias%20was%20being%20incorporated%20into%20the%20very%20constitution%20of%20the%20bench.%20Justice%20Arun%20Mishra%2C%20however%2C%20had%20rejected%20the%20allegation%20of%20conflict%20of%20interest%20by%20refusing%20to%20recuse%20from%20hearing%20the%20case%20in%20a%20separate%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2FLand_Acquisition_-_Recusal_Judgment.pdf%5C%22%3E%20judgment.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20recent%20example%20is%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20grant%20of%20bail%20to%20social%20activist%20Teesta%20Setalvad.%20A%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20comprising%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20A.S.%20Bopanna%20and%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F554-teesta-atul-setalvad-v-state-of-gujarat-19-jul-2023-483439.pdf%5C%22%3Egranting%3C%2Fa%3E%20bail%20to%20her%2C%20orally%20expressed%20their%20disagreement%20with%20the%20judgment%2C%20rendered%20by%20a%20previous%20bench%2C%20holding%20her%20guilty%20of%20abuse%20of%20process%2C%20after%20refusing%20to%20make%20her%20a%20party%20to%20the%20case%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2FJudgment-Zakia-Jafri-v-Gujarat.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EZakia%20Ahsan%20Jafri%20vs%20State%20of%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F26192910%2Fimage-183.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F26192910%2Fimage-183.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F26192910%2Fimage-183-300x183.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F26192910%2Fimage-183-1024x625.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-603826%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22733%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECrime%20branch%20officials%20produce%20social%20activist%20Teesta%20Setalvad%20at%20Metropolitan%20Magistrate%20Court%2C%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%20June%2026%2C%202022.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20judgment%20delivered%20last%20year%2C%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20A.M.%20Khanwilkar%2C%20Dinesh%20Maheshwari%20and%20C.T.%20Ravi%20Kumar%2C%20had%2C%20without%20naming%20Setalvad%20and%20other%20accused%2C%20indicted%20them%20in%20paragraph%2088%20for%20keeping%20the%20pot%20boiling%2C%20for%20ulterior%20design%2C%20in%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots%20cases%2C%20and%20insisted%20on%20proceeding%20against%20them%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20law%20after%20bringing%20them%20to%20the%20dock.%20The%20bench%20gave%20a%20clean%20chit%20to%20the%20present%20prime%20minister%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20who%20was%20then%20the%20Gujarat%20chief%20minister%2C%20by%20absolving%20him%20of%20any%20responsibility%20for%20the%20riots.%20The%20Gavai-Bopanna-Dipankar%20Datta%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20refrained%20from%20delving%20into%20those%20issues%20in%20its%20written%20judgment%2C%20for%20reasons%20of%20judicial%20propriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-renaming-commission-significance%5C%22%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20in%20a%20Name%3F%20Plenty%2C%20Says%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20Judgment%20We%20Must%20All%20Pay%20Heed%20To%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20polyvocal%20courts%20just%20propagators%20of%20judicial%20bias%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20never%20sits%20in%20its%20full%20strength%20as%20a%20panel%20of%2034%20judges.%20Instead%2C%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20the%20increasing%20number%20of%20cases%20due%20to%20the%20litigation%20boom%20in%20India%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2FOpinion%2FeKbYyaUBmyi7vSD0fuheoM%2FA-case-for-larger-benches.html%5C%22%3Eusually%3C%2Fa%3E%20sit%20in%20benches%20of%20two%20or%20three%2C%20in%20case%20of%20most%20judgments.%20This%20is%20argued%20to%20result%20in%20judges%20expressing%20their%20personal%20opinions%20through%20the%20judgments%20handed%20out%20by%20the%20benches.%20It%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2FOpinion%2FeKbYyaUBmyi7vSD0fuheoM%2FA-case-for-larger-benches.html%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20such%20polyvocality%20in%20India%20results%20in%20judgments%20becoming%20an%20embodiment%20of%20judicial%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20reason%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2017%2F04%2F01%2Fwhat-is-the-role-of-a-judge-in-a-polyvocal-court%2F%5C%22%3EGautam%20Bhatia%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20%E2%80%9Cbetter%20thought%20of%20not%20as%20a%20single%20%E2%80%9Ccourt%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20as%20many%20different%20courts%20of%20equal%20authority%2C%20who%20may%20often%20speak%20with%20different%20%E2%80%93%20or%20even%20opposed%20%E2%80%93%20voices%20on%20the%20same%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhatia%20cites%20the%20example%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalfreedomofexpression.columbia.edu%2Fcases%2Ftuljapurkar-v-maharashtra%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDevidas%20Tuljapurkar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20case%2C%20where%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20or%20not%20in%20the%20name%20of%20poetic%20license%20and%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20one%20could%20represent%20a%20historical%20figure%20by%20way%20of%20symbolism%20in%20an%20obscene%20manner%20arose.%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20ignored%20precedents%20of%20over%20the%20previous%2050%20years%20in%20defence%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20introduced%20a%20standard%20of%20obscenity%20applicable%20to%20only%20%E2%80%9Chistorically%20respectable%20personalities.%E2%80%9D%20The%20bench%20presided%20by%20him%20justified%20this%20by%20saying%20that%20the%20community%20standards%20become%20more%20stringent%20when%20used%20with%20regards%20to%20historically%20respected%20personalities%2C%20though%20he%20could%20cite%20no%20clear%20precedent%20to%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2Fsubramanian-swamy.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESubramanian%20Swamy%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2Fsubramanian-swamy.pdf%5C%22%3E%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Bhatia%20says%20that%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20upheld%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20criminal%20defamation%20as%20it%20stood%2C%20ignored%20the%20conflict%20that%20the%20ruling%20set%20up%20with%20the%20coordinate%20bench%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F501107%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ER.%20Rajagopal%20vs%20State%20of%20T%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Econcerning%20the%20different%20standards%20in%20civil%20and%20criminal%20defamation%20law%2C%20and%20invented%20a%20mythical%20doctrine%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20fraternity%E2%80%9D%20to%20justify%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20interim%20orders%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casemine.com%2Fjudgement%2Fin%2F5a65cbaf4a9326332077875d%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EShyam%20Narayan%20Chouksey%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20(the%20national%20anthem)%20case%2C%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20made%20the%20playing%20of%20the%20national%20anthem%20compulsory%20in%20cinemas%20before%20every%20film%20and%20thereby%20used%20judicial%20censorship%20to%20restrict%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20By%20directly%20restricting%20speech%2C%20it%20ensured%20that%20the%20deliberative%20process%20envisaged%20by%20the%20Constitution%20when%20it%20requires%20the%20State%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmake%20a%20law%E2%80%9D%20under%20Article%2019(2)%20was%20rendered%20chimerical%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20violated%20the%20separation%20of%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20judgment%20was%2C%20however%2C%20later%20modified%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F81046706%2F%5C%22%3Einterim%20orders%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Dipak%20Misra%2C%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20A.M.%20Khanwilkar%2C%20making%20the%20playing%20of%20the%20national%20anthem%20before%20the%20film%20by%20the%20cinema%20owners%20optional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20interim%20orders%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.legallyindia.com%2Fviews%2Fentry%2Fthe-supreme-court-hears-sabu-mathew-george-v-union-of-india-update%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESabu%20Mathew%20George%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20had%20passed%20interim%20orders%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cauto-blocking%E2%80%9D%20of%20keywords%20for%20sex%20determination%2C%20supposedly%20justified%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhmmeghalaya.nic.in%2Fprogrammes%2Fpcpndt%2Fact-pcpndt.pdf%5C%22%3EPre-Conception%20and%20Pre-Natal%20Diagnostic%20Techniques%20(PCPNDT)%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20was%20enacted%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20female%20foeticides%20and%20the%20declining%20sex%20ratio%2C%20but%20without%20any%20consideration%20of%20the%2019(1)(a)%20issues%20at%20play%20(including%20those%20of%20intermediary%20liability).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F27156_2016_3_1501_40744_Judgement_03-Jan-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAzam%20Khan%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20case%2C%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20had%20framed%20issues%20on%20whether%20political%20figures%20could%20be%20restrained%20from%20commenting%20on%20rape%20allegations%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20another%20invented%20doctrine%20labeled%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20compassion%E2%80%9D.%20In%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2016%2F27156%2F27156_2016_3_1501_40744_Judgement_03-Jan-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20Kaushal%20Kishore%20vs%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20five-Judge%20Constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20held%20that%20restrictions%20under%20Article%2019(2)%20are%20exhaustive%20and%20additional%20restrictions%20not%20found%20under%20this%20article%20cannot%20be%20imposed%20on%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20of%20an%20individual.%20The%20bench%20also%20held%20in%20this%20case%20that%20a%20statement%20made%20by%20a%20minister%20cannot%20be%20vicariously%20attributed%20to%20the%20Government%20by%20invoking%20the%20principle%20of%20collective%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20five%20cases%2C%20Bhatia%20had%20argued%2C%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20did%20not%20consider%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech%20to%20be%20of%20much%20value.%20That%20was%20his%20personal%20prerogative%3B%20however%2C%20when%20in%20case%20after%20case%2C%20brought%20to%20the%20Court%20through%20flimsy%20PILs%2C%20he%20passed%20judgments%20that%20place%20vast%20swathes%20of%20speech%20off%20limits%2C%20through%20the%20invention%20of%20new%20doctrines%20completely%20untethered%20from%20constitutional%20text%20and%20at%20odds%20with%20clear%20precedent%2C%20it%20became%20a%20serious%20problem%2C%20he%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20in%20ordinary%20circumstances%2C%20to%20implement%20his%20views%20on%20free%20speech%20(or%20the%20lack%20thereof)%2C%20Justice%20Misra%20would%20have%20had%20to%20convince%20a%20bench%20of%20five%20or%20seven%20judges%20to%20agree%20with%20him.%20However%2C%20as%20the%20senior%20judge%20in%20a%20two%20judge%20bench%2C%20he%20only%20has%20to%20convince%20one%20judge%20%E2%80%93%20and%20anyone%20who%20has%20spent%20any%20time%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20knows%20that%20puisne%20judges%20%3Cem%3Erarely%20%3C%2Fem%3Eassert%20themselves%20against%20senior%20judges%20(there%20are%20exceptions%2C%20of%20course)%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Gautam%20Bhatia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20majorly%20two-judge%20benches%2C%20these%20Supreme%20Court%20benches%20rarely%20ever%20result%20in%20split%20judgments%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcprindia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2FSSRN-id2061061.pdf%5C%22%3ENick%20Robinson%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20because%20as%20per%20tradition%2C%20junior%20benches%20usually%20succumb%20to%20the%20views%20of%20the%20senior%20benches%20except%20in%20cases%20when%20there%20is%20a%20clear%20violation%20of%20precedents.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20means%20fewer%20judges%20routinely%20express%20their%20individual%20opinion%2C%20decreasing%20the%20number%20of%20voices%2C%20and%20chances%20for%20conflict%2C%20on%20the%20court%2C%20%E2%80%9CRobinson%20further%20argues.%20Therefore%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20features%20of%20constitutional%20courts%20of%20decisions%20being%20made%20through%20a%20collegial%20process%20where%20opinions%20are%20shared%20and%20deliberated%20upon%20between%20judges%20of%20different%20views%2C%20disappear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20rights%20defender%2C%20the%20late%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2009%2F43%2Fcommentary%2Fideology-and-adjudication-supreme-court-and-obc-reservations.html%3F0%3Dip_login_no_cache%253D947282f1e28f608a92fc20d777fc96ac%5C%22%3EK.%20Balagopal%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20one%20of%20his%20articles%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20sad%20fact%20about%20the%20Indian%20judiciary%20is%20that%20where%20the%20judges%20have%20felt%20an%20urgent%20ideological%20compulsion%20they%20have%20not%20let%20mere%20canons%20of%20discipline%20stop%20them.%20Judgments%20by%20much%20smaller%20benches%20than%20nine%20have%20prised%20open%20what%20the%20nine-judge%20bench%20declared%20to%20be%20the%20law%20to%20such%20an%20extent%20%E2%80%93%20while%20paying%20lip%20service%20to%20their%20duty%20of%20obedience%20to%20it%20%E2%80%93%20that%20most%20of%20the%20issues%20are%20again%20open%20for%20rewriting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20systemic%20solutions%20suggested%20to%20remedy%20the%20ill-effects%20of%20polyvocal%20court%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Flead%2FFor-proximate-and-speedy-justice%2Farticle16297745.ece%5C%22%3EJustice%20P.N.%20Bhagwat%3C%2Fa%3Ei%20in%20%3Cem%3EBihar%20Legal%20Support%20Authority%20of%20India%20v%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20%26amp%3B%20Anr%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20was%20never%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20regular%20court%20of%20appeal%20against%20orders%20made%20by%20the%20high%20court%20or%20the%20sessions%20court%20of%20the%20magistrates.%20It%20was%20created%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20laying%20down%20the%20law%20for%20the%20entire%20country%20and%20the%20extraordinary%20jurisdiction%20of%20granting%20special%20leave%20was%20conferred%20upon%20it%20under%20Article%20136%20of%20the%20Constitution%20so%20that%20it%20could%20interfere%20whenever%20it%20found%20that%20the%20law%20was%20not%20correctly%20enunciated%20by%20the%20lower%20courts%20or%20tribunals%20and%20it%20was%20necessary%20to%20pronounce%20the%20correct%20law%20on%20the%20subject.%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelying%20on%20this%20judgment%2C%20many%20have%20suggested%20creation%20of%20an%20intermediate%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20between%20the%20high%20courts%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Former%20Attorney-General%20for%20India%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Flead%2FFor-proximate-and-speedy-justice%2Farticle16297745.ece%5C%22%3EK.K.%20Venugopal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20argued%20that%20setting%20up%20a%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20in%20each%20region%20would%20ensure%20that%20litigants%20can%20afford%20appeal%20at%20a%20much%20less%20expense.%20He%20further%20elucidates%20that%20proximity%20to%20the%20court%20of%20appeals%20will%20be%20%E2%80%9Ca%20boon%20to%20the%20common%20man.%E2%80%9D%20If%20such%20a%20proposal%20were%20to%20be%20accepted%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20would%20be%20able%20to%20hear%20cases%20in%20much%20larger%20numbers%20and%20offer%20their%20full%20deliberation%20to%20the%20cases%20they%20hear%2C%20he%20has%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20others%20have%20suggested%20using%20the%20existing%20constitutional%20provision%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-130-seat-of-supreme-court%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%20130%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20favour%20of%20setting%20up%20regional%20benches%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20While%20most%20former%20Chief%20Justices%20of%20India%20had%20expressed%20their%20reluctance%20to%20use%20this%20provision%2C%20equating%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20prestige%20with%20its%20only%20seat%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fjournal%2Fconstitution-bench-revival-breaking-ground-for-reform%2F%5C%22%3EN.V.%20Ramana%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20urged%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20set%20up%20regional%20benches%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20hear%20appeals%2C%20so%20that%20the%20Delhi%20bench%20could%20focus%20on%20cases%20regarding%20important%20constitutional%20matters.%20The%20former%20vice-president%20of%20India%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1586493%5C%22%3EVenkaiah%20Naidu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too%2C%20supported%20the%20demand%20for%20splitting%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20into%20four%20regional%20benches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D2189181%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20details%2C%20it%20has%20been%20shown%20that%20appeals%20from%20all%20across%20the%20country%20constituted%20over%2085%25%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20pendency%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20T.S.%20Thakur%2C%20during%20his%20tenure%20(2015-17)%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fbench-headed-by-cji-to-deliberate-on-setting-up-national-appeals-court%2Fstory-oybR3dNXUdQ7Yr2haSwo5K.html%5C%22%3Eagreed%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20hear%20a%20PIL%20filed%20by%20an%20advocate%2C%20V.%20Vasanthakumar%2C%20seeking%20setting%20up%20of%20a%20National%20Court%20of%20Appeal.%20This%20petition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fjonew%2Fjudis%2F43789.pdf%5C%22%3Ereferred%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20a%20Constitution%20Bench%20in%202016%2C%20and%20last%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2016%2F1543%2F1543_2016_1_503_37866_Order_30-Aug-2022.pdf%5C%22%3Elisted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20August%2030%20last%20year%2C%20has%20since%20been%20pending.%20The%20then%20Attorney%20General%2C%20K.K.%20Venugopal%2C%20too%2C%20supported%20the%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20reform%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20also%20align%20with%20the%20views%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-win-win-for-judges-people-756948.html%5C%22%3EB.R.%20Ambedkar%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%2C%20as%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Drafting%20Committee%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20envisaged%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20lay%20down%20answers%20to%20substantial%20questions%20of%20law%20and%20not%20function%20as%20an%20ordinary%20court%20of%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPending%20the%20drastic%20reform%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2017%2F04%2F01%2Fwhat-is-the-role-of-a-judge-in-a-polyvocal-court%2F%5C%22%3EGautam%20Bhatia%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99s%20suggestion%20that%20matters%20of%20constitutional%20nature%20be%20necessarily%20sent%20to%20five-judge%20courts%20instead%20of%20two-judge%20benches%2C%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20viable%20option%20to%20address%20the%20concerns%20over%20the%20polyvocal%20court%20at%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693825241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Findia-supreme-court-people-centric-polyvocal-image%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20perception%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20a%20polyvocal%20court%20has%20gained%20currency%20in%20recent%20years%20because%20there%20are%20too%20many%20judges%20sitting%20in%20different%20benches%20interpreting%20the%20law%20and%20the%20constitution%20in%20conflicting%20terms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Findia-supreme-court-people-centric-polyvocal-image%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SMART%20ePANTS%3A%20US%20intel%20invests%20heavily%20in%20'spy%20pants%2C%20undergarments'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693824662000%2C